The paper deals with the problem of channel estimation in massive MIMO systems, which is a topic of interest in the fields of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel scheme for DL channel tracking that involves the use of virtual channel representation, expectation maximization algorithm, and optimal Bayesian Kalman filter, which are techniques commonly used in these sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.LG.
